en_876170_0	The Colombo Municipal Council has planned to implement a car free day on next Sunday on several roads in Colombo City.
en_876170_1	It will be implemented jointly by the Colombo Municipal Council and the Netherlands Embassy.Plans have been drawn up to conduct the program on next Sunday on 6.00 a.m. to 12.00 noon from Independence Avenue to Green Path.
en_876170_2	The public can join the program with non-mechanical transport such as bicycles and skate boards.
en_876170_3	Colombo Mayor Rosy Senanayake said that it will not be an obstacle to walk, exercise or to engage in sports in those areas.
